15:
And I am exceedingly angry with the nations that are 
at ease; 
for while I was angry but a little, 
they furthered the disaster.

16:
These are the things that you shall do: 
Speak the truth to one another; 
render in your gates judgments 
that are true and make for peace;

5:
Ashkelon shall see it, and be afraid;
Gaza too, and shall writhe in anguish;
Ekron also, because its hopes are confounded.
The king shall perish from Gaza;
Ashkelon shall be uninhabited;
